    "# NB01 — Python Package Structure and Imports\n",
    "\n",
    "**Module 16 — Research Software Engineering**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Motivation\n",
    "\n",
    "Every notebook we have written so far either re-implements the same helper functions or copies them via copy-paste. This is a maintenance disaster: a bug fixed in one notebook stays broken in five others. The solution is a **package** — a directory of Python modules with a defined interface, importable from anywhere in the project. This notebook builds the skeleton of `compbio_utils`, the shared library that all subsequent notebooks in this module will populate.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Intuition\n",
    "\n",
    "A Python package is just a directory with an `__init__.py` file. When Python sees that file, it treats the directory as a namespace. Everything you put in `__init__.py` becomes available when someone writes `import compbio_utils`. Sub-files in the directory (`sequence.py`, `stats.py`) become submodules: `compbio_utils.sequence.gc_content()`.\n",
    "\n",
    "The `src/` layout adds one more directory level (`src/compbio_utils/`) to force a clean separation between the package source and the project root. This prevents accidental imports from the working directory instead of the installed package — a subtle bug that bites often in testing.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Biological Background\n",
    "\n",
    "Bioinformatics pipelines are collections of reusable operations: parse a FASTA file, compute GC content, find open reading frames, correct p-values. When these operations live in a shared library rather than duplicated scripts, a single improvement (e.g., a faster GC-content algorithm) propagates everywhere. This is the same principle behind Biopython, scikit-bio, and every major bioinformatics tool suite.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Mathematical / Conceptual Explanation\n",
    "\n",
    "There is no mathematics in this notebook — the content is purely structural. The key concepts are:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Namespace:** a mapping from names to objects. `compbio_utils.sequence` is a namespace.\n",
    "- **Relative import:** `from .sequence import gc_content` — the dot means \"same package.\"\n",
    "- **`__all__`:** a list of names exported when someone writes `from compbio_utils import *`. Explicit is better than implicit.\n",
    "- **`__version__`:** a string following semantic versioning (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH) that lets users and CI check which version is installed.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Computational Explanation\n",
    "\n",
    "Python's import system:\n",
    "1. Finds the package directory on `sys.path`.\n",
    "2. Executes `__init__.py`.\n",
    "3. Makes the package object available under the given name.\n",
    "\n",
    "With the `src/` layout, `pip install -e .` (editable install) puts `src/` on `sys.path` so that `import compbio_utils` resolves correctly from anywhere.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Python {sys.version}')\n",
    "print(f'Working directory: {Path.cwd()}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Package Directory Structure\n",
    "\n",
    "The target layout for `compbio_utils`:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "PACKAGE_TREE = \"\"\"\n",
    "utilities/\n",
    "└── compbio_utils/          ← project root (contains pyproject.toml)\n",
    "    ├── pyproject.toml      ← build system config + project metadata\n",
    "    ├── README.md\n",
    "    ├── CHANGELOG.md\n",
    "    ├── src/\n",
    "    │   └── compbio_utils/  ← the actual package\n",
    "    │       ├── __init__.py ← version + public API re-exports\n",
    "    │       ├── sequence.py ← DNA/RNA sequence utilities\n",
    "    │       ├── stats.py    ← statistical utilities\n",
    "    │       └── io.py       ← file I/O utilities\n",
    "    └── tests/\n",
    "        ├── conftest.py     ← shared fixtures\n",
    "        ├── test_sequence.py\n",
    "        ├── test_stats.py\n",
    "        └── test_io.py\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "print(PACKAGE_TREE)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Building the Package Skeleton"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import tempfile\n",
    "import textwrap\n",
    "\n",
    "# We build the skeleton in a temporary directory so this notebook is self-contained\n",
    "# In the real project, these files live in utilities/compbio_utils/\n",
    "tmpdir = Path(tempfile.mkdtemp(prefix='compbio_utils_skeleton_'))\n",
    "pkg_root = tmpdir / 'compbio_utils'\n",
    "src_pkg = pkg_root / 'src' / 'compbio_utils'\n",
    "tests_dir = pkg_root / 'tests'\n",
    "\n",
    "for d in [src_pkg, tests_dir]:\n",
    "    d.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f'Skeleton created at: {pkg_root}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# __init__.py — the package's public face\n",
    "init_content = textwrap.dedent(\"\"\"\n",
    "    \"\"\"compbio_utils — shared computational biology utilities.\n",
    "\n",
    "    This package provides sequence, statistics, and IO utilities\n",
    "    used across the computational biology curriculum.\n",
    "\n",
    "    Modules\n",
    "    -------\n",
    "    sequence : DNA/RNA sequence manipulation functions\n",
    "    stats    : Statistical utilities for genomics data\n",
    "    io       : File parsing and writing (FASTA, FASTQ, BED)\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    __version__ = '0.1.0'\n",
    "    __author__ = 'Vinoth'\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Re-export the most commonly used functions at the top level\n",
    "    from .sequence import reverse_complement, gc_content, kmer_frequencies\n",
    "    from .stats import bootstrap_ci, multiple_testing_correction\n",
    "    from .io import read_fasta, write_fasta\n",
    "\n",
    "    __all__ = [\n",
    "        '__version__',\n",
    "        'reverse_complement',\n",
    "        'gc_content',\n",
    "        'kmer_frequencies',\n",
    "        'bootstrap_ci',\n",
    "        'multiple_testing_correction',\n",
    "        'read_fasta',\n",
    "        'write_fasta',\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "\"\"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "(src_pkg / '__init__.py').write_text(init_content)\n",
    "print('Written: src/compbio_utils/__init__.py')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# sequence.py skeleton — full implementation in NB08\n",
    "sequence_content = textwrap.dedent(\"\"\"\n",
    "    \"\"\"Sequence utilities for DNA and RNA manipulation.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def reverse_complement(seq: str) -> str:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Return the reverse complement of a DNA sequence.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB08')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def gc_content(seq: str) -> float:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Compute the GC content of a DNA sequence as a fraction.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB08')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def kmer_frequencies(seq: str, k: int) -> dict:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Compute k-mer frequencies for a sequence.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB08')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def find_orfs(seq: str, min_length: int = 100) -> list:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Find all open reading frames in a DNA sequence.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB08')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def translate(seq: str) -> str:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Translate a DNA coding sequence to amino acids.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB08')\n",
    "\"\"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "(src_pkg / 'sequence.py').write_text(sequence_content)\n",
    "\n",
    "# stats.py skeleton\n",
    "stats_content = textwrap.dedent(\"\"\"\n",
    "    \"\"\"Statistical utilities for genomics data analysis.\"\"\"\n",
    "    import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def bootstrap_ci(data, stat_fn, n_boot=5000, alpha=0.05, rng=None):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Bootstrap confidence interval.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB09')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def multiple_testing_correction(pvalues, method='fdr_bh'):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Apply multiple testing correction.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB09')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def effect_size_cohens_d(group1, group2):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Compute Cohen's d effect size.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB09')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def log_fold_change(counts_a, counts_b, pseudocount=1):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Compute log2 fold change between two count vectors.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB09')\n",
    "\"\"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "(src_pkg / 'stats.py').write_text(stats_content)\n",
    "\n",
    "# io.py skeleton\n",
    "io_content = textwrap.dedent(\"\"\"\n",
    "    \"\"\"File I/O utilities for bioinformatics file formats.\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def read_fasta(filepath):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Parse a FASTA file, returning a dict of {header: sequence}.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB10')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def write_fasta(sequences, filepath):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Write a dict of sequences to a FASTA file.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB10')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def read_fastq(filepath):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Parse a FASTQ file, returning list of (name, seq, qual) tuples.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB10')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def parse_bed(filepath):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Parse a BED file into a pandas DataFrame.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB10')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "    def validate_sequence(seq, alphabet='DNA'):\n",
    "        \"\"\"Validate that a sequence contains only valid characters.\"\"\"\n",
    "        raise NotImplementedError('Implemented in NB10')\n",
    "\"\"\")\n",
    "\n",
    "(src_pkg / 'io.py').write_text(io_content)\n",
    "print('Written: sequence.py, stats.py, io.py (skeletons)')"
   ]
  },
